    "Evaluation": {
      "text": "Evaluate for alternative/reversible causes of AMS or exacerbating factors\nMRI\ncan be used to visualize the pontine lesion, with a characteristic \"batwing\" lesion of the pons appearing in typical cases",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "MRI",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Brain_MRI"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Management": {
      "text": "Desmopressin\nat 2 mcg q6 hrs IV/SC\n6 mL/kg of 5% dextrose in water, repeated until serum sodium rise back below 9 mEq in 24 hrs\nIf concerns for iatrogenic rapid increase in serum Na concentration (IV crystalloid bolus before Na lab comes back):\nStop IV fluids, send urine osmolality, repeat serum Na\nIf uOsm is < 100 mOsm/L, this suggests free water diuresis\nOr if sodium appears to be on a trajectory to increase >8mEq/L in 24hrs\nAdminister DDAVP 1 mcg x1",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "Desmopressin",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/Desmopressin"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Disposition": {
      "text": "Admit",
